to ask you.

362
00:34:58,580 --> 00:35:00,172
It's nothing hard or anything.

363
00:35:00,300 --> 00:35:05,169
I'm gonna go and look
for somebody...

364
00:35:05,300 --> 00:35:09,373
And I want you to stand...
like a sort of a guard, OK?

365
00:35:15,220 --> 00:35:17,495
Now, you can't mess up.

366
00:35:17,620 --> 00:35:19,019
A lot might depend on this.

367
00:35:19,140 --> 00:35:20,812
I won't screw up.

368
00:35:20,940 --> 00:35:22,453
Turn off the light.

369
00:35:27,500 --> 00:35:29,491
Here's what we're going to do.

370
00:35:29,620 --> 00:35:30,939
It's dark in here.

371
00:35:31,060 --> 00:35:33,449
And it's not
what you're thinking.

372
00:36:24,300 --> 00:36:25,653
Are you still watching?

373
00:36:28,180 --> 00:36:29,533
Yeah. So?

374
00:36:29,660 --> 00:36:30,615
I'm just checking.

375
00:38:13,740 --> 00:38:15,253
Watch out!

376
00:38:16,780 --> 00:38:17,610
Watch out!

377
00:38:45,660 --> 00:38:47,890
Wake up!

378
00:38:49,620 --> 00:38:52,293
Are you there?

379
00:38:52,420 --> 00:38:53,853
I'm here.

380
00:39:22,460 --> 00:39:25,816
Nancy, help me, please.

381
00:39:25,940 --> 00:39:27,089
Save me from...

382
00:39:27,220 --> 00:39:28,369
Freddy!

383
00:39:38,060 --> 00:39:39,573
This is just a dream.

384
00:39:39,700 --> 00:39:40,815
This isn't real.

385
00:39:40,940 --> 00:39:42,293
This is just a dream.

386
00:39:42,420 --> 00:39:44,012
He isn't real.

387
00:40:32,620 --> 00:40:35,771
Glen, you bastard.

388
00:40:35,900 --> 00:40:37,174
What did I do?

389
00:40:37,300 --> 00:40:39,450
I just
asked you to do one thing...

390
00:40:39,580 --> 00:40:41,571
Just stay awake and watch me...

391
00:40:41,700 --> 00:40:45,375
Just wake me up if it looked
like I was having a bad dream...

392
00:40:45,500 --> 00:40:46,728
And what did you do?

393
00:40:46,860 --> 00:40:48,532
You shit.

394
00:40:48,660 --> 00:40:49,809
You fell asleep.

395
00:40:51,420 --> 00:40:52,296
Oh, shit.

396
00:40:52,420 --> 00:40:53,978
Hurry.

397
00:40:54,100 --> 00:40:57,615
Shut up and stay there.
Don't go away.

398
00:41:02,900 --> 00:41:03,810
Are you OK?

399
00:41:03,940 --> 00:41:06,738
Yeah. It was just
a little dream, that's all.

400
00:41:06,860 --> 00:41:08,976
I'm going right back to sleep.

401
00:41:09,100 --> 00:41:11,091
Call me if you need anything.

402
00:41:28,460 --> 00:41:30,655
You mind telling me
what's going on?

403
00:41:30,740 --> 00:41:32,253
Just come on.

404
00:41:34,180 --> 00:41:37,889
Garcia, I've got to see
Rod Lane again.

405
00:41:37,980 --> 00:41:39,459
You know,
I took the night shift...

406
00:41:39,580 --> 00:41:41,332
So I could get
some peace and quiet.

407
00:41:41,460 --> 00:41:42,495
It's urgent!

408
00:41:58,740 --> 00:42:00,378
We have reason to believe
that there might be...

409
00:42:00,500 --> 00:42:02,138
Something very strange
going on here.

410
00:42:02,260 --> 00:42:03,693
Got no argument with that.

411
00:42:03,820 --> 00:42:05,378
What are you doing here?

412
00:42:05,500 --> 00:42:06,819
There's an unsolved murder...

413
00:42:06,940 --> 00:42:08,453
And I don't like
unsolved murders...

414
00:42:08,580 --> 00:42:10,616
Especially ones that
my daughter' s mix ed up in.

415
00:42:10,740 --> 00:42:11,934
What are you doing here?

416
00:42:12,060 --> 00:42:13,652
At this hour,
you should be home in bed.

417
00:42:13,780 --> 00:42:15,293
I just want to see if he's OK.

418
00:42:15,420 --> 00:42:17,331
Nancy, take my word for it.

419
00:42:17,460 --> 00:42:18,813
The guy's sleeping like a baby.

420
00:42:18,940 --> 00:42:20,009
He's not going anywhere.

421
00:42:27,980 --> 00:42:29,698
Just go down and look at him.

422
00:42:32,260 --> 00:42:33,329
Please, Daddy.

423
00:42:35,220 --> 00:42:36,494
All right.

424
00:42:36,620 --> 00:42:38,736
Garcia, give me the keys.

425
00:42:38,860 --> 00:42:40,179
Right.

426
00:42:41,340 --> 00:42:43,490
Where the hell
did I put the keys?

427
00:43:00,380 --> 00:43:03,019
Help! Help!

428
00:43:12,380 --> 00:43:13,256
Jesus!

429
00:43:20,380 --> 00:43:21,608
Cut him down.

430
00:43:23,220 --> 00:43:24,494
Grab his legs.

431
00:43:24,620 --> 00:43:26,258
I got him.

432
00:43:31,540 --> 00:43:33,337
Grab his back, would you?

433
00:43:33,460 --> 00:43:34,449
Lower him.

434
00:43:57,940 --> 00:43:59,214
Ashes to ashes...

435
00:43:59,340 --> 00:44:00,614
Dust to dust.

436
00:44:00,740 --> 00:44:03,049
May God be
with this young man's soul.

437
00:44:05,500 --> 00:44:07,855
His life and his death...

438
00:44:07,980 --> 00:44:10,938
Attest to
the scriptures' warning...

439
00:44:11,060 --> 00:44:14,336
That he who lives by the sword
shall die by the sword.

440
00:44:14,460 --> 00:44:17,657
But let us recall also
our Lord's admonition...

441
00:44:17,780 --> 00:44:23,571
That we judge not,
lest we be judged.

442
00:44:23,700 --> 00:44:26,373
And may Rod Lane rest in peace.

443
00:44:31,780 --> 00:44:33,338
Time to go, honey.

444
00:44:40,180 --> 00:44:41,056
Hop in.

445
00:44:44,340 --> 00:44:46,171
The killer' s still loose,
you know?

446
00:44:46,300 --> 00:44:49,531
You're saying somebody else
killed Tina?

447
00:44:49,660 --> 00:44:50,570
Who?

448
00:44:50,700 --> 00:44:53,931
I don't know who he is...

449
00:44:54,060 --> 00:44:57,973
But he's burned,
and he wears a weird hat...

450
00:44:58,100 --> 00:45:02,457
And a red and green sweater,
really dirty...

451
00:45:02,580 --> 00:45:06,175
And he uses these knives,
like giant fingernails.

452
00:45:09,980 --> 00:45:12,050
You better keep her home
for a few days...

453
00:45:12,180 --> 00:45:13,533
Until she really gets
over the shock of this.

454
00:45:13,660 --> 00:45:14,979
I've got something better.

455
00:45:15,100 --> 00:45:17,330
I'm going to get her some help.

456
00:45:41,300 --> 00:45:43,495
I don't see why you couldn't
just give me a pill...

457
00:45:43,620 --> 00:45:44,735
To keep me from dreaming.

458
00:45:44,860 --> 00:45:46,771
Everyone's got to dream,
young lady.

459
00:45:46,900 --> 00:45:50,256
If you don't dream, you go.

460
00:45:50,380 --> 00:45:51,369
All set.

461
00:45:53,340 --> 00:45:56,537
Please, Nancy, trust us.

462
00:45:56,660 --> 00:45:59,572
It's not you I don't trust.
It's just...

463
00:46:07,860 --> 00:46:10,135
Let's do it.

464
00:46:15,060 --> 00:46:16,413
Thank you, nurse.

465
00:46:33,380 --> 00:46:34,938
How long has this been going on?

466
00:46:35,060 --> 00:46:37,176
Since the murders.

467
00:46:37,300 --> 00:46:39,177
She was fine before that.

468
00:46:39,300 --> 00:46:41,609
Now she thinks
her dreams are real.

469
00:46:41,740 --> 00:46:45,176
There's no sign
of pathology in her EEG.

470
00:46:45,300 --> 00:46:47,734
I'd guess that what we have
is just a normal girl...

471
00:46:47,860 --> 00:46:49,930
Who happens to have gone
through two days of hell.

472
00:46:58,900 --> 00:47:01,175
